  "title": "Stroke of Genius: Pantomime Masturbation Throughout Performing Arts History",
  "description": "Sharp intellectual satire meets risqué Monty Python buffoonery in this polished multimedia \"lecture.\" Our deadpan Professor \"makes a surprisingly lucid case\" [Orlando Sentinel] regarding the historical and academic significance of . . . clowns pretending to masturbate. This semester, you can take \"JACKIN' AROUND\" very seriously.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Head writer: Vulva Va-Voom, Staff writer: Shane Mayforth<br><strong>Cast</strong>: Starring Shane Mayforth as Dr. Walter Winkworth-Perez, with Vulva Va-Voom as The Spankin' Shyster<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Sausage conveyance mechanism by GutterFly Productions<br/></br>",
  "website": "https://boiledhorse.com",
  "plain_language": "\"Stroke of Genius\" is about a college professor who teaches a strange academic subject. Throughout theater history, clowns and mimes have mimicked many types of humorous behavior. This professor specializes in pantomimed masturbation. Dr. Walter Winkworth-Perez has spent many years studying theories and techniques of these comedic performers. His lesson plans put a special focus on the 1920s silent film actor who is recognized as the all-time greatest star of the art form.",
